thread.title: Blue Devils clip Chiefs

author: Staff reports
title: Blue Devils clip Chiefs
text: Sault Ste. Marie Evening News - Sault Ste. Marie, MI By Staff reports Posted Oct. 7, 2015 at 10:48 AM By Staff reports Posted Oct. 7, 2015 at 10:48 AM CHEBOYGAN — Sault High dealt Cheboygan its first conference loss of the season, spilling the Chiefs 25-15, 25-21, 25-18 Tuesday night. Cece Werner hit 13 kills, and added nine digs and five blocks for the Blue Devils, who took over the lead in the Straits Area Conference. Jordan Menard had five kills and 10 digs, while Ella Rechner had six kills and four blocks. Maddi Misiak turned in nine digs and six kills, and Val Gage had six kills Jacki Sanderson dished out 28 assists and had 10 digs, while Brenna James added a team-best 29 digs. “Great team effort,” Sault High coach Lisa Moran said. “Everybody stepped up and played to level we are capable of playing at. High intensity, definitely best games we played all season. Sophomore Werner returned to the Sault lineup after missing a little more than a week with an ankle injury. “Nice to have Cece back, she played great,” Moran said. “Brenna played amazing tonight and Ella Rechner really stepped up her game. We played a well-rounded game where everyone contributed.” Sault High has a home match scheduled against Escanaba Saturday. Cheboygan 2, Sault 1: The Chiefs won the JV match 25-22, 9-25, 15-13. Kristen LaPrade delivered 11 kills and 13 digsf or the Sault. Rachel Ayers had nine kills, three digs and one block, while Ashtyn Bell added four kills, one dig and one block. Katja Wilhelms handed out 25 assists and had four aces, two digs, one kill and one block, while Kayla Wilhelms added two kills, two aces and nine digs. Bays sweep Bulldogs BRIMLEY— The Brimley Bays swept past Rudyard 25-22, 25-22, 25-21 in an Eastern UPConference volleyball match Tuesday night. Kaylee Hill had 18 assists, three kills and one ace for the Bays. Mallorie Kronemeyer hit nine kills and had three blocks and two aces, while Alyssa Hyvarinen added seven kills, five blocks and one ace. Adele Healey added four kills and one assist, while Cassie Tessmer had 11 kills and an assist, and Julia Stenglein had one kill, one block and one assist. Katya Rozelle added 11 digs, and Delaney Walden had 13 assists for the Bays. By Staff reports Sault Ste. Marie Evening News - Sault Ste. Marie, MI By Staff reports
